Content:
@jorian that's my thinking at the momemt because we all want to keep the election process as decentralized as possible, so thus an independent website works nicely. That gitbook tools seems really useful here as with it all candidates can push updates to the website independently. We will look into that more.

There is also a lot of content we could have on that website, and it is much more focused when it's sitting on its own site versus being on the main Komodo domain. On the new rebrand website we can have a short section about notary nodes / elections, and then link to the official election site/process (based on Github).

Makes sense? üòÉ
